# zwire HUD patch series — applied in order by fork/apply-patches.sh.
#
# Phase 1 patches (authored against the checked-out pinned tree, compile-tested).
# Each entry is a path relative to fork/patches/. Uncomment as each is authored.
#
0001-tab-shape-hud.patch            # tab_style_views.cc GetPath -> sharp ~2px HUD tabs (VERIFIED git-apply @150.0.7871.46)
0002-ui-colors-hud.patch            # chrome_color_mixer.cc/.h + chrome_color_mixers.cc -> HUD palette on frame/toolbar/omnibox/tabs; ends with AddZwireHudFinalMixer (dead-last) re-asserting tab colors so the Material/native tab-strip mixers can't leave the active tab a scheme-independent GM3 default ("always red" tab) (VERIFIED git-apply @150.0.7871.46)
0003-ui-font-mono-hud.patch            # resource_bundle.cc -> Share Tech Mono / Monaco UI font (VERIFIED)
0004-toolbar-neon-border.patch      # toolbar_view.cc -> neon border + glow (VERIFIED git-apply @150.0.7871.46)
0005-omnibox-hud.patch              # location_bar_view.cc -> HUD field styling (VERIFIED git-apply @150.0.7871.46)
0006-branding-strings.patch         # chrome/app/theme/chromium/BRANDING -> "zwire" product strings (VERIFIED git-apply @150.0.7871.46)
0007-devtools-hud-theme.patch       # devtools front_end (3 files) -> 8 HUD schemes in the Theme dropdown (VERIFIED git-apply @150.0.7871.46)
# 0008-tmux-split-prefix.patch — REMOVED (file deleted). The native 2-pane
#   side-by-side split was "fake" tmux; real N-pane tiling is the JS overlay
#   (extensions/hud-internal/ztmux.js), which owns Ctrl-b. The old patch consumed
#   the prefix + the next key before the page saw them (the "C-b %%" double-tap).
0008-allow-framing.patch          # ancestor_throttle.cc -> allow framing any site (tmux iframes)
0009-ext-command-focus-webcontents.patch  # extension_keybinding_registry_views.cc -> when an extension command fires while chrome UI (the omnibox/search bar) has focus, hand focus to the page web contents so the ⌘K palette overlay is typeable (VERIFIED @150.0.7871.46)
0010-newtab-force-zwire.patch       # search.cc -> chrome://newtab always resolves to the zwire newtab extension (never the default Google NTP) when it's loaded (VERIFIED @150.0.7871.46)
0011-pinned-extensions-always-show.patch  # toolbar_view.cc -> hold the extensions container at preferred width so pinned actions never drop to the puzzle overflow on runtime re-pin (VERIFIED @150.0.7871.46)
0012-allow-frame-src.patch          # navigation_request.cc -> a host page CSP frame-src/child-src never blocks a sub-frame nav (tmux iframes embed any site) (VERIFIED @150.0.7871.46)
0013-default-restore-last-session.patch  # session_startup_pref.cc -> default startup = restore last session (auto-restore tabs)
0014-no-session-crashed-bubble.patch    # session_crashed_bubble_view.cc -> never show the "Restore pages?" crash bubble (auto-restore instead)
0015-no-navigation-block.patch       # extension_navigation_throttle.cc -> never block a chrome-extension:// nav for a not-yet-registered extension (startup NTP-override page)
0016-ext-private-api-allowlist.patch # _permission_features.json -> allowlist hud-internal (DCE846DF…) for developerPrivate (widens extension_types to include "extension") + settingsPrivate, so the HUD Extensions/Settings pages get chrome.developerPrivate/settingsPrivate (VERIFIED git-apply @150.0.7871.46)
0017-no-hold-to-quit.patch          # app_controller_mac.mm runConfirmQuitPanel -> force hold-⌘Q-to-quit OFF (immediate quit) regardless of kConfirmToQuitEnabled, which a synced profile can flip back on
0018-ext-dispatch-null-policy-container.patch # extension_function_dispatcher.cc -> gate the is_sandboxed UMA probe on RenderFrameHost::IsActive() so an extension-function IPC from a non-active frame (null policy_container_host_) can't hit active_sandbox_flags()'s NOTREACHED (crbug.com/455908853); fixes the SIGTRAP when a content script calls a chrome.* API on chromewebstore.google.com mid-navigation (VERIFIED git-apply+reverse @150.0.7871.46)
0019-ext-script-webstore.patch        # chrome_extensions_client.cc IsScriptableURL -> drop the gallery special-case (kCannotScriptGallery) so extension content scripts + tabs.executeScript run on the Chrome Web Store domains (chrome.google.com/webstore + chromewebstore.google.com) like any other page; store-privileged JS bindings stay gated by IsWebstoreOrigin in permissions_data.cc (VERIFIED git-apply+reverse @150.0.7871.46)
0020-hud-native-menu-colors.patch     # chrome_color_mixer.cc AddZwireHudFinalMixer -> bind the ui::kColorMenu* family (app/three-dot menu, context menus, dropdowns) to the HUD Sys tokens (kColorSysBaseContainer/…OnSurface/…Outline) so native Views menus follow the scheme + light/dark toggle instead of the NativeTheme default that left light text on a light bg (unreadable app menu in light mode). References, not literals — depends on 0002's Sys-token block (VERIFIED git-apply+reverse @150.0.7871.46)
0021-hud-native-primitive-colors.patch # chrome_color_mixer.cc AddZwireHudFinalMixer -> systemic mode fix: HUD light mode recolors Sys tokens but never flips NativeTheme, so core_default_color_mixer builds every native-Views primitive (kColorPrimary/Secondary/DisabledForeground, kColorPrimaryBackground, kColorEndpointBackground, kColorMidground) from the OS color_mode -> dialogs/bubbles/dropdowns/textfields/labels/tooltips invert when HUD and OS modes disagree. Rebind those primitives to the HUD-mode-aware Sys tokens so the whole native surface tree tracks HUD light/dark + scheme in one place. Generalizes 0020; references, not literals (VERIFIED git-apply+reverse @150.0.7871.46)
